name: Broiled Salmon with Asparagus and Lime-Butter Sauce

steps.instruction:
### Steps
1. Preheat oven on broil
2. Line baking sheet with foil
3. Zest lime (1 teaspoon) and squeeze for juice (1 tablespoon). Coat salmon with zest and 1/2 teaspoon seasoning (wash hands)
4. Coat salmon and asparagus with spray; arrange in single layer on baking sheet, then broil on center rack for 6 minutes
5. Move baking sheet to top rack; broil 12 more minutes or until vegetables are tender and salmon is opaque and flakes easily.
6. Meanwhile, microwave cauliflower rice following package instructions. Melt butter
7. Place juice, garlic, honey, and remaining 1/4 teaspoon seasoning in blender (or food processor); slowly pour in butter while blender is running, until sauce forms. Serve salmon over cauliflower rice and asparagus; top with sauce
